extends ui_layout

block content

  .ui.text.container
    br
    h2 Digital Literacy and Fake News Post-Activity Quiz
    form#lit_post.ui.reply.form(action='/postquiz/digital-literacy', method='POST')
      input(type='hidden', name='_csrf', value=_csrf)
      .ui.form
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='assignment_post') What's one way to tell whether a fact you see online is real or fake?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='assignment_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label It includes a lot of numbers and statistics, even if it doesn't say where they came from.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='assignment_post', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label It gives information about where the fact came from or who discovered it.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='assignment_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label If everyone says it's real, it probably is.
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='news_post') What are some strategies that people use to get you to click on news stories?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='news_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Give their stories titles that make you curious about what the story says.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='news_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Use images, videos, numbers, or "facts" that seem unbelievable or too good to be true.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='news_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Use images or words are shocking or that create strong emotions.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='news_post', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label All of the above.
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='stopping_post') What are things you can do to help other people distinguish between real and fake news or websites? 
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='stopping_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Remind them to check the facts. It's easy to do a Google search to check whether something really happened.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='stopping_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Remind them to look for accurate website addresses. Sometimes people set up news sites that mimic trustworthy sites, but are actually fake.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='stopping_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Remind them to check the "about us" section of a website. It might indicate whether a site is satire or real.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='stopping_post', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label All of the above.
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='social_post') Your friend Milo tells you that dinosaurs can hatch from chicken eggs, and that he saw a video about it on Facebook. Do you believe him?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='social_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Yes - Milo gets really good grades in science class, so I trust him.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='social_post', tabindex='0', value='0')
            label Yes - Facebook wouldn't lie.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='social_post', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label No - anyone can post anything on Facebook, whether it's true or not. Plus that just doesn't make sense!

        h2 Just a few more questions... There are no right or wrong answers here!
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='like') How much did you like this activity?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='like', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label I didn't like it at all.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='like', tabindex='0', value='2')
            label Not very much, but it wasn't awful.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='like', tabindex='0', value='3')
            label A little bit, it was neither good nor bad.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='like', tabindex='0', value='4')
            label Some - it was god but not amazing.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='like', tabindex='0', value='5')
            label A lot - it was awesome!
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='friends') Would you recommend this activity to your friends?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='friends', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label No, not at all.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='friends', tabindex='0', value='2')
            label Maybe.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='friends', tabindex='0', value='3')
            label Yes, I would!
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='length') What did you think of the length of the activity?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='length', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label It was too short.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='length', tabindex='0', value='2')
            label It was just the right length.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='length', tabindex='0', value='3')
            label It was too long.
        .grouped.fields
          label(for='understand') Do you think you understand the issues of information literacy and fake news better after completing the activity?
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='understand', tabindex='0', value='1')
            label Yes, I understand the issues better.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='understand', tabindex='0', value='2')
            label I'm not sure.
        .field
          .ui.radio.checkbox
            input.hidden(type='radio', name='understand', tabindex='0', value='3')
            label No, I didn't learn anything.
        br
        button.ui.button(type='submit') Submit
        br
        br
        br
